Deep Learning & NLP Projects
Content Based Adaptive News Recommender System Flask Application
A Flask-based application that fetches relevant news articles using a News API.
Users can explore news articles through a Random News generator feature or by
selecting specific categories.( Users need to provide their API key to access the
app). Articles are displayed within the app using iframes (please note some major
sites may block iframes).
The app adapts to users' news preferences and suggests personalized articles by
storing their preferences in a SQLite database. Currently, BERT algorithm is used
for this purpose.
Future improvements include experimenting with a collaborative and adaptive
recommender system architecture and upgrading the app database to a vector-
search or semantic-search-based database for enhanced contextual
understanding
Current Feature Components & Technologies used :
Backend Database: SQLite, News Category Classifier: Cosine Similarity technique,
Adaptive News Recommender Feedback: TF-IDF and Semantic NLP algorithms like
BERT
Internship Projects: Full Stack Machine Learning Applications (Containerized &
Deployed along with API endpoints)
